00:45:49.000 --> 00:46:09.000
Is that this boy that used to iron mothers, saris was, um, um, but as a domestic assistant, uh, it first came to sahaja in India and he was very ill because he was working in an, in a factory for with the chemicals for, for make for manufacturing medicine.

293
00:46:09.000 --> 00:46:13.000
So from, from young age, he did that job. We had, he nailed so many chemicals.

294
00:46:13.000 --> 00:46:15.000
He was really very sick and now he could not work.

295
00:46:15.000 --> 00:46:17.000
So mother gave him realization.

296
00:46:17.000 --> 00:46:24.000
And then, uh, mother told him also, I think you better find a different job, you know, but, um, it was not easy for him to find a different job.

297
00:46:24.000 --> 00:46:28.000
I think even his parents, you know, depending on, depended a bit on his income.

298
00:46:28.000 --> 00:46:33.000
Uh, you know, it's very hard to know to find a new career and your job and everything.

299
00:46:33.000 --> 00:46:36.000
So we asked mother, really mother, please, uh, can you give me a job?

300
00:46:36.000 --> 00:46:47.000
You know, I think he must have assumed mother had lots of jobs because size yoga is a big organization and people don't realize that, uh, you know, people don't get paid on jobs going in size yoga.

301
00:46:47.000 --> 00:46:51.000
But you really mother, please, you know, please, can you give me a job?

302
00:46:51.000 --> 00:46:55.000
You know, and mother said, uh, what are the profession would you like to do?

303
00:46:55.000 --> 00:46:57.000
You know, he said, cooking.

304
00:46:57.000 --> 00:46:58.000
Oh, do you know how to cook?

